Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225%g} and fry until
browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up into equal-sized large
chunks, roughly 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, halve the @ciabatta{1}.

Once the sausage meat has browned, stir in the @butter beans{1%carton},
@Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder),
@creme fraiche{150%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and
@water{200%ml} for the sauce.

Transfer to the top shelf of your oven and bake until thickened and bubbling,
~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausage meat is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

A few mins before everything's ready, toast the ciabatta halves in your
#toaster{} until golden.

Once toasted, drizzle with a little @olive oil{}.

When your cassoulet has finished baking, remove from the oven and stir through
the @baby spinach{40%g} until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Share the sausage and bean cassoulet between your #bowls{}.

Serve the ciabatta alongside for dipping. Enjoy!